# Mickmumpitz Compositing ADV v01
## How it works:
## ISOLATE GROUP

Import a video into the “Load Video” node. Choose how you want to remove the background:
1 Segment anything (Recommended) Type in a prompt for the object/subject you want to isolate e.g. man, woman, person…

or
2 Upload your own .png sequence with alpha channel Set your resolution in the “image Resize node”.
## BACKGROUND GROUP
Choose if you want to use an image, a video or an image sequence as background below. You can activate the “Lens Blur” node if you want to blur your background.
## MODELS

For this workflow you will need:

- Any SD1.5 model (I’m using photon_v01)

- The LCM LoRA SD1.5 Lora (Search “LCM” in the Model Manager)

- IC-Light/fbc (Search “ic-light” in the Model Manager)

- ControlNet-v1-1 (tile; fp16; v11u) (Search “controlnet” in the Model Manager)

- [Animate LCM](https://huggingface.co/wangfuyun/AnimateLCM/tree/main)

- or recommended: v3_sd15_mm (Search “v3” in the Model Manager)

Activate Reactor nodes if your face looks too different. This can happen if you re-diffuse the entire image or your subject is far away from the camera. Not recommended for close-ups!
